WEBVTT

1
00:01:52.322 --> 00:01:56.272
www.NapiProjekt.pl - nowa jakość napisów.
Napisy zostały specjalnie dopasowane do Twojej wersji filmu.

2
00:01:56.322 --> 00:01:57.322
Hey. Pop.

3
00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.996
Been a while. hasn't it?

4
00:02:02.079 --> 00:02:04.290
Did you see that motorcade roll up?

5
00:02:04.373 --> 00:02:09.612
It's the first time that
the President of the United States

6
00:02:09.638 --> 00:02:11.807
has visited Gaffney.

7
00:02:11.890 --> 00:02:13.975
Can you believe it?

8
00:02:14.977 --> 00:02:16.937
Oh. I wouldn't be here
if I had a choice.

9
00:02:17.021 --> 00:02:18.856
But I have to do these
sort of things now.

10
00:02:18.939 --> 00:02:20.482
Makes me seem more human.

11
00:02:20.566 --> 00:02:23.778
And you have to be a little human
when you're the president.

12
00:02:23.861 --> 00:02:26.364
He couldn't even afford
to pay for his own gravestone.

13
00:02:26.447 --> 00:02:30.910
I paid for it out of my own
scholarship money from The Sentinel.

14
00:02:30.993 --> 00:02:33.913
Nobody showed up
for his funeral except me.

15
00:02:33.996 --> 00:02:35.998
Not even my mother.

16
00:02:39.960 --> 00:02:42.212
But I'll tell you this. though. Pop:

17
00:02:42.296 --> 00:02:46.175
when they bury me.
it won't be in my backyard.

18
00:02:46.258 --> 00:02:49.511
And when they come
to pay their respects.

19
00:02:49.595 --> 00:02:52.014
they'll have to wait in line.

20
00:02:57.519 --> 00:02:59.646
You should let us
take a photo at the grave.

21
00:02:59.730 --> 00:03:03.650
He wants privacy. The man's
honoring his father. for God's sakes.

22
00:03:17.168 --> 00:04:53.905
<font color="#3399CC">Subtitles by </font><font color="ffffff">MemoryOnSmells</font>
<font color="#3399CC">http://UKsubtitles.ru.</font>

23
00:04:55.387 --> 00:04:58.015
Here's the info
you were looking for.

24
00:04:58.098 --> 00:05:03.770
And we have that scheduled
for next Tuesday at 10 a.m.

25
00:05:03.854 --> 00:05:06.565
That's still good for you. right?

26
00:05:06.648 --> 00:05:09.067
Excellent. I'll confirm it.

27
00:05:12.779 --> 00:05:14.239
Excuse me.

28
00:05:14.323 --> 00:05:15.616
Yes. sir?

29
00:05:15.699 --> 00:05:17.201
Yes. sir.

30
00:05:17.284 --> 00:05:19.286
The president is ready to see you now.

31
00:05:23.415 --> 00:05:24.416
Jesus.

32
00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:28.170
I'm devastated.

33
00:05:30.005 --> 00:05:31.924
I love this man as if he were my son.

34
00:05:33.759 --> 00:05:37.846
Now. he's a fighter.
and I'm sure that he'll pull through.

35
00:05:37.930 --> 00:05:39.765
Our prayers are with him.

36
00:05:39.848 --> 00:05:43.727
"...said President Underwood
during a press conference yesterday.

37
00:05:44.728 --> 00:05:48.815
The Maryland State Police and
Federal authorities have yet to locate

38
00:05:48.899 --> 00:05:52.110
Mr. Stamper's car or name any suspects."

39
00:05:54.613 --> 00:05:56.782
You want more of this. brother?

40
00:05:59.368 --> 00:06:01.370
Or maybe the sports page?

41
00:06:07.292 --> 00:06:12.881
"Game Six of the World Series
went scoreless for 13 innings

42
00:06:12.965 --> 00:06:16.802
before a rain delay that turned
an already epic evening

43
00:06:16.885 --> 00:06:19.096
into one for the history books."

44
00:06:57.384 --> 00:06:59.219
We need a doctor
in room three-one.

45
00:06:59.302 --> 00:07:00.804
Douglas?

46
00:07:01.680 --> 00:07:03.640
Can you hear me?

47
00:07:04.558 --> 00:07:07.144
I want you to blink if you can hear me.

48
00:07:12.274 --> 00:07:13.859
Again.

49
00:07:18.613 --> 00:07:20.782
My name is Dr. Lanjwani.

50
00:07:20.866 --> 00:07:23.577
The president's office asked me
to look after you personally.

51
00:07:23.660 --> 00:07:26.204
You're getting the very best
of care. okay?

52
00:07:27.914 --> 00:07:31.126
Douglas. I want you to blink
if you can feel this.

53
00:07:35.505 --> 00:07:37.841
Good. Good.

54
00:07:37.924 --> 00:07:39.676
How about this?

55
00:07:41.553 --> 00:07:42.888
Okay. Excellent.

56
00:07:43.764 --> 00:07:45.182
And this?

57
00:07:49.227 --> 00:07:51.438
How about here?

58
00:07:55.817 --> 00:07:57.235
Relax.

59
00:07:57.319 --> 00:08:00.739
Relax.
Perfectly normal at this early stage.

60
00:08:00.822 --> 00:08:02.074
Relax.

61
00:08:02.157 --> 00:08:03.992
That's good.

62
00:08:04.076 --> 00:08:06.411
Okay. Get some rest.

63
00:08:32.687 --> 00:08:34.356
Are you gonna hurt me?

64
00:08:35.065 --> 00:08:37.984
I will do whatever you want.
please just don't hurt me.

65
00:08:38.068 --> 00:08:40.320
- Does that hurt?
- A little.

66
00:08:40.404 --> 00:08:43.115
All right. let's go ahead.
Try and make a fist for me.

67
00:08:43.198 --> 00:08:44.866
- Remy.
- What's that?

68
00:08:44.950 --> 00:08:47.869
Remy Danton. Was he here?

69
00:08:47.953 --> 00:08:50.163
He was.
Just checking on your progress.

70
00:08:50.247 --> 00:08:52.707
Go ahead. make that fist for me.

71
00:09:00.715 --> 00:09:04.594
Oh...

72
00:09:04.678 --> 00:09:06.179
- Lion.
- Mm-hm.

73
00:09:06.263 --> 00:09:08.265
Rhinoceros.

74
00:09:08.348 --> 00:09:10.058
- Camel.
- Good.

75
00:09:10.142 --> 00:09:11.893
What color is Rudolph's nose?

76
00:09:15.147 --> 00:09:17.732
- Rudolph?
- Reindeer.

77
00:09:19.651 --> 00:09:21.153
Red.

78
00:09:23.530 --> 00:09:25.073
It's red.

79
00:09:25.157 --> 00:09:27.409
The President of the United States?

80
00:09:31.163 --> 00:09:32.581
Douglas?

81
00:09:32.664 --> 00:09:35.083
Who is the President
of the United States?

82
00:09:39.296 --> 00:09:41.173
Frank Underwood.

83
00:09:42.591 --> 00:09:44.384
- What year are we in?
- 2014.

84
00:09:44.468 --> 00:09:46.303
What month is it?

85
00:09:48.680 --> 00:09:50.515
It's December.

86
00:09:58.690 --> 00:10:00.650
I have to get back to work.

87
00:10:02.194 --> 00:10:04.488
Douglas. Listen to me.

88
00:10:04.571 --> 00:10:08.366
- You suffered a compound fracture...
- I know what I fucking suffered!

89
00:10:09.201 --> 00:10:11.161
I need you to hear me this time.

90
00:10:12.829 --> 00:10:15.665
There was damage
to your left frontal cortex.

91
00:10:15.749 --> 00:10:21.004
Your motor skills will be a struggle.
Your emotions will be unpredictable.

92
00:10:21.087 --> 00:10:24.090
There's a long road ahead.
and we can't rush it.

93
00:10:26.968 --> 00:10:28.970
- Let's do the test later.
- No.

94
00:10:30.889 --> 00:10:32.641
We'll finish it now.

95
00:10:35.018 --> 00:10:36.478
What was your mother's name?

96
00:10:36.561 --> 00:10:39.147
She was young and beautiful.

97
00:10:39.231 --> 00:10:43.193
Jacob fell in love with her
while she was watering a lamb. and...

98
00:10:43.276 --> 00:10:46.363
she became his wife
after he worked seven years

99
00:10:46.446 --> 00:10:48.657
to earn her hand in marriage.

100
00:10:51.243 --> 00:10:54.621
Push back.
Heel into my hand.

101
00:10:56.790 --> 00:10:58.667
Breathe.

102
00:10:58.750 --> 00:11:01.127
Back up. Deep breath.
Ready?

103
00:11:03.171 --> 00:11:06.633
Push. Push.

104
00:11:06.716 --> 00:11:09.177
Hey. Doug.

105
00:11:09.261 --> 00:11:10.804
Focus.

106
00:11:12.555 --> 00:11:14.516
The report I submit to Congress today

107
00:11:14.599 --> 00:11:18.436
includes evidence that would normally
warrant criminal prosecution.

108
00:11:18.520 --> 00:11:21.022
but the Justice Department
won't pursue charges

109
00:11:21.106 --> 00:11:23.900
in accordance
with the presidential pardons.

110
00:11:23.984 --> 00:11:26.945
I'm grateful for the hard work
Ms. Dunbar and her team

111
00:11:27.028 --> 00:11:29.698
have dedicated to their investigation.

112
00:11:29.781 --> 00:11:32.701
In response. I'll be forming
a bipartisan commission to examine

113
00:11:32.784 --> 00:11:36.246
campaign finance reform
so history does not repeat itself.

114
00:11:36.329 --> 00:11:39.040
and so that our nation can heal
from these wounds.

115
00:11:39.124 --> 00:11:41.209
I got bacon-cheese and regular.
Which one you want?

116
00:11:41.293 --> 00:11:42.502
Just a minute.

117
00:11:43.295 --> 00:11:47.590
Remember when you'd never eat a burger
if it didn't have bacon on it?

118
00:11:47.674 --> 00:11:51.678
Dad would get so pissed because he hated
the smell of bacon grease on the grill.

119
00:11:51.761 --> 00:11:53.179
I'm trying to listen. Gary.

120
00:11:53.263 --> 00:11:56.433
The president's hands
are tied. Might as well let him burn.

121
00:11:56.516 --> 00:11:58.643
They're getting their
marshmallows ready.

122
00:11:58.727 --> 00:12:00.812
Look at Underwood's approval rating.

123
00:12:00.895 --> 00:12:02.856
It's worse than Walker's
before he resigned.

124
00:12:02.939 --> 00:12:05.233
That's a deep. deep hole
to climb out of.

125
00:12:05.317 --> 00:12:07.235
The Republicans are gonna
have their fun for a while.

126
00:12:07.319 --> 00:12:10.488
Plenty to hammer him on
in the general. And they're out for blood.

127
00:12:10.572 --> 00:12:12.615
They lost big on education
and entitlement reform.

128
00:12:12.699 --> 00:12:15.327
And if the rumors
about America Works are true...

129
00:12:15.410 --> 00:12:17.329
For the left.
that's just too far to the right

130
00:12:17.412 --> 00:12:19.039
and for the right.
it's too far to the left.

131
00:12:19.122 --> 00:12:21.374
They need me back.

132
00:12:21.458 --> 00:12:23.251
Where? The White House?

133
00:12:23.335 --> 00:12:26.212
We got to turn the corner.
start ramping up for 2016.

134
00:12:26.296 --> 00:12:27.589
He might turn this around.

135
00:12:27.672 --> 00:12:29.591
You don't really think
he's gonna win. do you?

136
00:12:29.674 --> 00:12:31.343
The guy's experienced.
Underwood has a lot...

137
00:12:31.426 --> 00:12:33.094
He'll recover.

138
00:12:33.178 --> 00:12:35.680
He's a behind-the-scenes guy.
He's not comfortable in the spotlight.

139
00:12:35.764 --> 00:12:39.768
- How about you recover first?
- ...glad-handing and kissing babies.

140
00:12:39.851 --> 00:12:42.812
This is gonna be a long 18 months
if this proves any indication.

141
00:12:42.896 --> 00:12:46.232
It can be a lot of chest-thumping
but nothing really getting done.

142
00:12:46.316 --> 00:12:49.736
The Xybenetrin
will help with depression.

143
00:12:49.819 --> 00:12:52.405
The buspirone is for anxiety.
Here you go.

144
00:12:55.492 --> 00:12:59.371
I'd like to prescribe you something
for the pain. but with your...

145
00:12:59.454 --> 00:13:01.748
Well. any patient with a history
of addictive behavior...

146
00:13:01.831 --> 00:13:04.667
I know. It's fine.

147
00:13:04.751 --> 00:13:06.336
I can handle the pain.

148
00:13:38.326 --> 00:13:40.036
He looks a lot better.

149
00:13:41.413 --> 00:13:43.289
No. he's still asleep.

150
00:13:45.917 --> 00:13:47.419
I have to go.

151
00:13:47.502 --> 00:13:48.670
Okay.

152
00:13:49.754 --> 00:13:51.881
Is this a bad time?

153
00:13:53.508 --> 00:13:55.009
No. It's fine.

154
00:13:55.093 --> 00:13:57.303
No. it's just no one told me
you were coming.

155
00:13:59.055 --> 00:14:01.683
Hi. Francis sends his love.

156
00:14:01.766 --> 00:14:03.935
He would visit himself.
but with the media...

157
00:14:04.018 --> 00:14:05.895
No. I understand.

158
00:14:05.979 --> 00:14:08.940
He did come before. when...

159
00:14:09.816 --> 00:14:11.317
- Both of us.
- I know.

160
00:14:11.401 --> 00:14:13.194
I saw the flowers.
Thank you.

161
00:14:13.278 --> 00:14:15.071
- You look well.
- I'm getting there.

162
00:14:15.155 --> 00:14:17.240
I just want to get better
so I can get back to work.

163
00:14:17.323 --> 00:14:19.701
We're looking forward to that.

164
00:14:20.368 --> 00:14:22.871
We can use all the help
we can get. actually.

165
00:14:22.954 --> 00:14:24.497
Yeah. Been watching the news.

166
00:14:24.581 --> 00:14:27.834
Francis. he's at his wit's end.
The Republicans...

167
00:14:27.917 --> 00:14:30.712
won't send him a single bill
he can sign.

168
00:14:30.795 --> 00:14:33.506
- And the Democrats aren't much better.
- Bob Birch?

169
00:14:33.590 --> 00:14:36.342
Blind leading the stupid.

170
00:14:37.927 --> 00:14:39.888
How's Remy working out?

171
00:14:39.971 --> 00:14:44.225
Well. we'd much rather have you there.
but he's doing a fine job.

172
00:14:46.060 --> 00:14:49.481
Doug. do you... recall anything?

173
00:14:49.564 --> 00:14:51.649
- About what happened?
- Why?

174
00:14:51.733 --> 00:14:53.026
Did the police find something?

175
00:14:53.109 --> 00:14:56.196
Not that we're aware of. And we've
asked them to hold off questioning you

176
00:14:56.279 --> 00:14:58.406
until you're feeling more like yourself.

177
00:15:01.618 --> 00:15:04.871
Rachel. she...

178
00:15:09.751 --> 00:15:11.836
I don't remember.

179
00:15:12.712 --> 00:15:14.881
Yes. you do.

180
00:15:19.511 --> 00:15:21.930
A carjacking.

181
00:15:22.013 --> 00:15:24.224
- A man.
- What sort of man?

182
00:15:24.307 --> 00:15:26.267
That part's fuzzy.

183
00:15:26.351 --> 00:15:28.228
It could be anyone. then.
Any man.

184
00:15:28.311 --> 00:15:30.563
Yeah. Any man.

185
00:15:30.647 --> 00:15:33.900
- And he got frightened?
- I chased him and that's all.

186
00:15:36.569 --> 00:15:40.532
- Any idea where she is?
- No.

187
00:15:40.615 --> 00:15:43.409
Because it's important that we find her.

188
00:15:45.578 --> 00:15:46.913
I really don't know.

189
00:15:48.498 --> 00:15:49.666
That's the truth.

190
00:15:53.628 --> 00:15:57.131
I want you to tell all of this
to the police. exactly what you told me.

191
00:15:57.215 --> 00:15:59.926
about the carjacking and the man.
Nothing about her.

192
00:16:00.009 --> 00:16:01.719
I got it.

193
00:16:01.803 --> 00:16:05.056
If you need anything.
or remember anything...

194
00:16:09.060 --> 00:16:11.646
- It's good to see you.
- You. too.

195
00:16:35.628 --> 00:16:38.131
That's good. One more time.
Up and forward. That's good.

196
00:16:38.214 --> 00:16:39.966
Excellent. Breathe.

197
00:16:40.049 --> 00:16:41.509
Good.

198
00:16:41.593 --> 00:16:43.094
Good. Good.

199
00:16:45.263 --> 00:16:46.806
Okay.

200
00:16:46.890 --> 00:16:50.101
Let's try this one.
You're doing a great job.

201
00:16:51.603 --> 00:16:53.605
Keep breathing. Good.

202
00:16:54.689 --> 00:16:56.232
Good job. Doug.

203
00:16:57.901 --> 00:17:01.321
Okay. Moving forward.
You got it.

204
00:17:01.404 --> 00:17:02.780
Great. Great job.

205
00:17:02.864 --> 00:17:04.198
Keep going.

206
00:17:05.033 --> 00:17:06.492
Good. Breathe.

207
00:17:08.661 --> 00:17:10.371
Excellent. Good.

208
00:17:10.455 --> 00:17:12.498
One more.

209
00:17:12.582 --> 00:17:14.042
Great job.

210
00:17:14.125 --> 00:17:15.919
One more time.
It's almost done. Ready?

211
00:17:16.002 --> 00:17:17.337
Keep breathing.

212
00:17:17.420 --> 00:17:19.881
Just his voice.
He said. "Get out of the car."

213
00:17:19.964 --> 00:17:21.841
Anything you can say about the voice?

214
00:17:21.925 --> 00:17:25.428
Was it. uh...
Accent? Lisp? High? Low?

215
00:17:25.511 --> 00:17:27.180
Deep.

216
00:17:28.056 --> 00:17:29.098
That's all I remember.

217
00:17:31.017 --> 00:17:33.269
Then I laid on the horn. I...

218
00:17:35.021 --> 00:17:37.106
I remember him running.

219
00:17:37.190 --> 00:17:39.275
Like a blur. I got out.

220
00:17:40.068 --> 00:17:41.903
I chased him.

221
00:17:44.739 --> 00:17:46.366
I'm not sure. I must have...

222
00:17:47.367 --> 00:17:49.577
What were you doing
in that part of Maryland?

223
00:17:53.957 --> 00:17:55.375
Mr. Stamper?

224
00:17:55.458 --> 00:17:58.670
Sir. What were you doing
in that part of Maryland?

225
00:18:01.547 --> 00:18:03.591
I drive sometimes to think.

226
00:18:03.675 --> 00:18:06.719
There was a lot on my mind with work.
I drive to clear my head.

227
00:18:09.472 --> 00:18:11.307
Have you found the car?

228
00:18:12.225 --> 00:18:14.811
We don't have anything
other than what you just told us.

229
00:18:19.399 --> 00:18:21.442
How's your mood been?
Any episodes?

230
00:18:21.526 --> 00:18:22.735
No. The meds are working.

231
00:18:22.819 --> 00:18:24.278
You just telling me what I want to hear?

232
00:18:24.362 --> 00:18:27.198
No. I feel good.

233
00:18:27.281 --> 00:18:28.491
Okay.

234
00:18:28.574 --> 00:18:31.327
I'm gonna sign your release today.

235
00:18:31.411 --> 00:18:34.497
But it's important
you take it easy at first.

236
00:18:34.580 --> 00:18:36.749
Everything's gonna be
much harder in general.

237
00:18:36.833 --> 00:18:37.959
I know.

238
00:18:38.042 --> 00:18:39.585
Do you have someone
who can look after you?

239
00:18:39.669 --> 00:18:42.046
Yeah. My brother Gary's in from Ohio.

240
00:18:42.130 --> 00:18:43.965
Good. How long is he here for?

241
00:18:44.048 --> 00:18:47.218
- A while. I guess.
- Okay. great.

242
00:18:47.301 --> 00:18:51.264
It's important you go to your meetings.
Stay on top of your sobriety.

243
00:18:52.932 --> 00:18:56.394
Take this.
It's for the steroids I prescribed you.

244
00:18:56.477 --> 00:19:00.940
It's one shot into the right thigh.
once a week. The nurse. she...

245
00:19:01.024 --> 00:19:02.400
- She showed me how.
- Okay.

246
00:19:23.129 --> 00:19:25.048
You do this?

247
00:19:25.131 --> 00:19:26.841
No. it wasn't me.

248
00:19:55.787 --> 00:19:57.121
I talked to my boss.

249
00:19:57.205 --> 00:20:00.291
I can stick around
for another couple of weeks

250
00:20:00.374 --> 00:20:03.127
- while you transition back.
- You should get back to your family.

251
00:20:03.211 --> 00:20:04.754
Nah... Sarah's fine with it.

252
00:20:04.837 --> 00:20:06.297
The kids are. too.

253
00:20:06.380 --> 00:20:09.425
Gary. we've hardly spoken in ten years.

254
00:20:09.509 --> 00:20:12.011
You've already gone above and beyond.

255
00:20:12.637 --> 00:20:16.057
All right.
You want me to go?

256
00:20:17.058 --> 00:20:18.059
I'm fine.

257
00:20:19.060 --> 00:20:21.312
Thanks for everything.

258
00:20:21.395 --> 00:20:22.688
Okay.

259
00:20:22.772 --> 00:20:26.067
I mean. I'm just a phone call
and a plane ticket away.

260
00:20:33.157 --> 00:20:34.742
Safe travels.

261
00:20:35.910 --> 00:20:37.870
Uh...

262
00:20:37.954 --> 00:20:39.288
Take care.

263
00:20:44.252 --> 00:20:46.212
Hey. Gary. I...

264
00:20:49.048 --> 00:20:50.591
Send me some pictures of the kids.

265
00:20:53.386 --> 00:20:54.887
Yeah. I will.

266
00:21:07.984 --> 00:21:10.736
But one of the things I admire
about you is that in Washington. DC.

267
00:21:10.820 --> 00:21:13.364
which is so gridlocked.
you get things done.

268
00:21:13.447 --> 00:21:16.367
And I understand you've got. um.
a new piece of legislation.

269
00:21:16.450 --> 00:21:19.162
a major new initiative
you're rolling out. What is it?

270
00:21:19.245 --> 00:21:22.748
That is correct. It's a new jobs program
that we're calling America Works.

271
00:21:22.832 --> 00:21:26.544
Oh. So it's a fantasy novel.

272
00:21:26.627 --> 00:21:28.588
This is
a fundamentally different look

273
00:21:28.671 --> 00:21:31.007
at how to solve
the problem of unemployment.

274
00:21:31.090 --> 00:21:34.010
It has the size
and the scope of the New Deal.

275
00:21:34.093 --> 00:21:37.346
Oh. So it's a socialist
redistribution of wealth

276
00:21:37.430 --> 00:21:40.016
wherein the baby boomers
will latch onto the millennials

277
00:21:40.099 --> 00:21:43.853
like a lamprey and just keep sucking
until they're as dry as a crouton?

278
00:21:46.314 --> 00:21:48.232
This is about
putting people to work

279
00:21:48.316 --> 00:21:50.568
and avoiding the entitlements entirely.

280
00:21:50.651 --> 00:21:52.069
Well. I like the sound of that.

281
00:21:52.153 --> 00:21:54.113
So what. we're gonna
privatize Social Security

282
00:21:54.197 --> 00:21:57.116
and then raise revenue
by hunting the elderly for sport?

283
00:21:58.576 --> 00:22:00.578
- Good plan. Use that.
- No. as I said.

284
00:22:00.661 --> 00:22:02.872
this is a fundamentally
different approach entirely.

285
00:22:02.955 --> 00:22:06.125
And you think that the Republicans
in Congress will cooperate with you?

286
00:22:06.209 --> 00:22:10.296
Oh. I think that it has been proved
that both parties want the same thing.

287
00:22:10.379 --> 00:22:13.257
A new president in 2016?

288
00:22:13.341 --> 00:22:17.511
No. No. I think actually.
I think unemployment. eradicating it.

289
00:22:17.595 --> 00:22:20.139
and I think a strong economy
is something both parties want.

290
00:22:20.223 --> 00:22:23.476
Okay. speaking of everyone.
there's a recent poll by Reuters.

291
00:22:23.559 --> 00:22:26.103
I wanna get this right.
It says that eight out of ten Americans

292
00:22:26.187 --> 00:22:29.815
agree that you lack. quote.
"effectiveness and leadership."

293
00:22:29.899 --> 00:22:32.693
Uh. look.
I don't let polls like that bother me.

294
00:22:32.777 --> 00:22:35.905
I think that once the nation
sees AmWorks in action.

295
00:22:35.988 --> 00:22:39.408
- they will change their attitudes.
- I'm sorry. "AmWorks?"

296
00:22:39.492 --> 00:22:41.532
I'm sorry... I didn't realize
it was called AmWorks.

297
00:22:41.535 --> 00:22:44.205
Is that like Amway?
Is it a pyramid scheme?

298
00:22:44.288 --> 00:22:46.415
Is that what you're selling
the American people?

299
00:22:46.499 --> 00:22:49.502
No. it's actually just an abbreviation
to make it easier to say.

300
00:22:49.585 --> 00:22:53.506
Well. if you make it small enough.
uh. maybe it'll be easier to swallow.

301
00:22:56.842 --> 00:22:59.553
You know. even though
you're a Democrat. I respect you.

302
00:22:59.637 --> 00:23:02.264
But let's just take a look
at the facts here for a second.

303
00:23:02.348 --> 00:23:06.268
You've been president for six months.
and again. I wanna get this right.

304
00:23:06.352 --> 00:23:09.689
unemployment has gone up. our trade
deficit with China has increased.

305
00:23:09.772 --> 00:23:11.774
the number of vetoes has skyrocketed.

306
00:23:11.857 --> 00:23:14.443
I'm not entirely sure that I'm confident

307
00:23:14.527 --> 00:23:17.947
that you'll be able to eradicate
unemployment the same way

308
00:23:18.030 --> 00:23:20.616
you've been able
to eradicate your approval polls.

309
00:23:20.700 --> 00:23:22.785
What. you know. what do you...

310
00:23:22.868 --> 00:23:25.538
How are you going to get it across
to the American people?

311
00:23:40.970 --> 00:23:43.806
- Doug?
- Seth?

312
00:23:43.889 --> 00:23:46.058
Yeah. it's me.

313
00:23:46.142 --> 00:23:48.227
Mrs. Underwood.
she gave me this phone. but...

314
00:23:48.310 --> 00:23:50.104
I know. Is something wrong?

315
00:23:51.147 --> 00:23:53.899
No. I want to speak to the president.

316
00:23:53.983 --> 00:23:55.568
Is it urgent?

317
00:23:55.651 --> 00:23:57.653
I want to talk to him
about the America Works program.

318
00:23:57.737 --> 00:24:00.489
- So nothing urgent.
- It's not an emergency. no.

319
00:24:00.573 --> 00:24:02.908
'Cause that's what this phone is for.

320
00:24:04.910 --> 00:24:06.537
Will you pass on my message?

321
00:24:39.028 --> 00:24:42.490
Ah!

322
00:25:28.369 --> 00:25:29.620
Hey.

323
00:25:32.498 --> 00:25:33.499
You're late.

324
00:25:33.582 --> 00:25:36.001
I switched cabs three times.

325
00:25:36.085 --> 00:25:39.171
- Were you being followed?
- Didn't want to take chances.

326
00:25:41.924 --> 00:25:44.802
- You know why I asked you here.
- I don't know where she is.

327
00:25:44.885 --> 00:25:47.596
- Then you need to find out.
- I ran her social. her name.

328
00:25:47.680 --> 00:25:49.473
police records. taxes. everything.

329
00:25:49.557 --> 00:25:52.143
She could be tossed in a ditch
by a john for all I know.

330
00:25:52.226 --> 00:25:54.603
- You work at the FBI.
- What do I get in return?

331
00:25:54.687 --> 00:25:56.605
My protection. like you asked.

332
00:25:56.689 --> 00:25:59.191
I thought you had something to offer.
Something real.

333
00:25:59.275 --> 00:26:00.609
Like money?

334
00:26:00.693 --> 00:26:04.530
Like getting me out of the Bureau. You
make that happen. maybe I can help you.

335
00:26:04.613 --> 00:26:07.700
That was a condition.
for your charges being dropped.

336
00:26:11.162 --> 00:26:13.330
See. you don't still know people.

337
00:26:14.999 --> 00:26:18.127
- I shouldn't have even come here.
- I am your only safety net.

338
00:26:18.210 --> 00:26:20.629
You think I would have turned over
all the AT&T records

339
00:26:20.713 --> 00:26:22.298
without leaving a backup with somebody?

340
00:26:22.381 --> 00:26:25.050
I'm not gonna blow my get-out-of-jail
card on a wild goose chase.

341
00:26:27.803 --> 00:26:29.889
Does anyone suspect anything?

342
00:26:29.972 --> 00:26:31.432
At the Bureau?

343
00:26:33.309 --> 00:26:35.311
Nobody has a clue about her.

344
00:26:35.394 --> 00:26:37.521
If that gives you any peace of mind.

345
00:26:55.414 --> 00:26:56.540
Doug?

346
00:26:56.624 --> 00:26:58.792
Tell him it's urgent.

347
00:26:58.876 --> 00:27:00.669
We're aiming for sometime in May.

348
00:27:00.753 --> 00:27:03.297
As soon as we agree on a date
with the Russian delegation.

349
00:27:03.380 --> 00:27:06.091
you will be the first to know. Uh. Greg.

350
00:27:06.175 --> 00:27:07.843
The Summit with Petrov
here in Washington.

351
00:27:07.927 --> 00:27:09.678
what'll be the focus of the talks?

352
00:27:09.762 --> 00:27:11.889
A bilateral approach to the Middle East.

353
00:27:11.972 --> 00:27:14.266
As you know. the Palestinians
have refused to negotiate

354
00:27:14.350 --> 00:27:16.393
until Israeli troops
leave the Jordan Valley.

355
00:27:16.477 --> 00:27:19.146
We hope to address
this with President Petrov

356
00:27:19.230 --> 00:27:21.523
so that we can move on
to a whole host of other issues.

357
00:27:21.607 --> 00:27:22.441
Sara.

358
00:27:22.524 --> 00:27:25.402
So this bilateral approach doesn't
include Israel and Palestine.

359
00:27:25.486 --> 00:27:27.988
The State Department
is briefing all interested parties.

360
00:27:28.072 --> 00:27:30.324
The summit's really just a first step.
Ayla.

361
00:27:30.407 --> 00:27:32.618
I'd like to change course
to the America Works program.

362
00:27:32.701 --> 00:27:33.577
Please.

363
00:27:33.661 --> 00:27:35.981
I've spoken to a number
of the president's policy advisors.

364
00:27:35.996 --> 00:27:38.540
who say there's been a lot
of disagreement on the economic team

365
00:27:38.624 --> 00:27:41.627
as to exactly what form
this jobs package should take.

366
00:27:41.710 --> 00:27:43.587
- Which advisors?
- Nice try.

367
00:27:43.671 --> 00:27:47.758
To be clear. this is far more
than just a jobs package.

368
00:27:47.841 --> 00:27:52.554
It is a comprehensive plan. which aims
at full employment within two years.

369
00:27:52.638 --> 00:27:55.015
So as such. there are a lot
of details to be worked out.

370
00:27:55.099 --> 00:27:56.892
So your sources are inaccurate.

371
00:27:56.976 --> 00:27:58.936
It's not so much a disagreement

372
00:27:59.019 --> 00:28:01.897
as it is debating the finer points
of the plan. Jess.

373
00:28:01.981 --> 00:28:04.441
Just to follow up.
What are some of the finer points?

374
00:28:04.525 --> 00:28:07.278
Or the broad strokes. even. No one
from the White House has said anything.

375
00:28:07.361 --> 00:28:10.239
When we have a plan to present.
we will present it.

376
00:28:10.322 --> 00:28:11.907
Jess?

377
00:28:11.991 --> 00:28:15.411
Is America Works a reaction
to the president's low approval ratings?

378
00:28:15.494 --> 00:28:18.289
An effort to offer some sign of progress
ramping up to the elections?

379
00:28:18.372 --> 00:28:20.173
We've been working on this plan
since day one.

380
00:28:20.207 --> 00:28:21.875
It has nothing to do
with the approval ratings.

381
00:28:21.959 --> 00:28:25.212
But as for the election...
uh. whose turn is it to ask today?

382
00:28:25.296 --> 00:28:28.799
- Mark?
- Is the president running in 2016?

383
00:28:28.882 --> 00:28:31.969
Today. the priority
is good government. but...

384
00:28:32.052 --> 00:28:34.555
Ask me again tomorrow.

385
00:28:34.638 --> 00:28:36.390
Thank you. everyone.

386
00:28:37.850 --> 00:28:39.393
We've got a window at ten.

387
00:28:39.476 --> 00:28:40.978
I'll call him now.

388
00:28:45.107 --> 00:28:46.859
Please. sit down.

389
00:28:47.860 --> 00:28:49.278
John. Samantha.

390
00:28:49.361 --> 00:28:52.156
You spoke to a journalist
about disagreements in this room?

391
00:28:52.239 --> 00:28:54.408
If that happens again.
you're off the team.

392
00:28:54.491 --> 00:28:56.869
And speaking of the disagreements
in this room.

393
00:28:56.952 --> 00:28:59.955
we now have an even bigger one.
because Remy has shown me

394
00:29:00.039 --> 00:29:03.000
your work so far and...

395
00:29:03.083 --> 00:29:04.877
it's toothless.

396
00:29:04.960 --> 00:29:09.006
I stood in this room three months ago
and gave you all very clear direction.

397
00:29:09.089 --> 00:29:11.842
Social Security. Medicare. Medicaid.

398
00:29:11.925 --> 00:29:14.762
every entitlement program
that is sucking us dry.

399
00:29:14.845 --> 00:29:18.057
I want it all on the table.
And this doesn't go nearly far enough.

400
00:29:18.140 --> 00:29:20.684
So we obviously have
to get back to some basics.

401
00:29:20.768 --> 00:29:23.854
Remind ourselves of some of the facts
that are before us...

402
00:29:23.937 --> 00:29:26.065
- Sir. if I may...
- No. no. no. no.

403
00:29:27.399 --> 00:29:31.195
I will speak first.
and then you will speak. Paul.

404
00:29:34.615 --> 00:29:37.117
This is what
the average senior citizen gets.

405
00:29:37.201 --> 00:29:39.119
one year from entitlements.

406
00:29:39.203 --> 00:29:41.705
whether they were a janitor
or they ran a hedge fund.

407
00:29:41.789 --> 00:29:45.584
That... This money is a job

408
00:29:45.668 --> 00:29:48.921
we could be giving to a single mother
or a student just out of school.

409
00:29:49.004 --> 00:29:50.381
Now. at the moment.

410
00:29:50.464 --> 00:29:54.802
44 cents of every tax dollar
goes to pay for these programs.

411
00:29:54.885 --> 00:29:58.055
By 2030. it'll be over half. 62 cents.

412
00:29:58.138 --> 00:30:00.891
Entitlements are bankrupting us.

413
00:30:00.974 --> 00:30:03.352
Now. I had Remy conduct a little poll.

414
00:30:03.435 --> 00:30:05.729
Statement posed was:
"Doing what's best for my country

415
00:30:05.813 --> 00:30:07.398
means doing some things
that I don't like."

416
00:30:07.481 --> 00:30:09.900
Seventy-four percent agreed
with this statement.

417
00:30:09.983 --> 00:30:13.612
Seventy-four percent.
Now. what does that tell us?

418
00:30:13.696 --> 00:30:17.825
We have to do the things
that people won't like.

419
00:30:17.908 --> 00:30:21.537
And even when we do. three out of four
of them will go along with us.

420
00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:24.456
And why?
Because we're promising jobs.

421
00:30:24.540 --> 00:30:27.543
And again. where are the three areas

422
00:30:27.626 --> 00:30:30.921
that we're gonna be
creating these jobs from?

423
00:30:31.004 --> 00:30:33.966
Infrastructure at the state
and federal level.

424
00:30:34.049 --> 00:30:36.051
Increasing the size of the military.

425
00:30:36.135 --> 00:30:38.535
and working with our friends
in the private sector to start...

426
00:30:38.554 --> 00:30:41.056
I'm sorry. sir.
but I have to interrupt.

427
00:30:41.140 --> 00:30:44.309
The programs that you want
to scale back or dismantle

428
00:30:44.393 --> 00:30:46.729
are the bedrock
of the American dream.

429
00:30:46.812 --> 00:30:48.480
You work hard. you pay your taxes...

430
00:30:48.564 --> 00:30:51.483
No. I'm sorry. they were
the bedrock of the American dream.

431
00:30:51.567 --> 00:30:53.152
But they're not anymore.

432
00:30:53.235 --> 00:30:56.280
Certainly not for the ten million people
who are out of work.

433
00:30:56.363 --> 00:30:59.575
But practically speaking.
a thousand special interests.

434
00:30:59.658 --> 00:31:02.202
organized labor.
opposition in both parties.

435
00:31:02.286 --> 00:31:05.205
Now. we can do a version
of what you're proposing...

436
00:31:05.289 --> 00:31:08.000
I don't want a version.

437
00:31:08.083 --> 00:31:10.335
I want a vision.

438
00:31:11.295 --> 00:31:15.466
As head of this team.
and I think I speak for everyone.

439
00:31:15.549 --> 00:31:18.343
- we have done...
- Speaking as the president.

440
00:31:18.427 --> 00:31:21.221
who chose this team
and for whom it works.

441
00:31:21.305 --> 00:31:26.351
I want five hundred billion dollars
to put ten million people to work.

442
00:31:26.435 --> 00:31:28.270
I don't care how much it hurts.

443
00:31:28.353 --> 00:31:30.731
I don't care how controversial it is.

444
00:31:30.814 --> 00:31:33.442
Your job is to find a way.

445
00:31:33.525 --> 00:31:37.654
It's my job to convince Congress
and the American people.

446
00:31:37.738 --> 00:31:42.701
Your job is not to sell me
on your version of my program.

447
00:31:43.744 --> 00:31:46.330
Now. are we all clear
on what our jobs are?

448
00:31:46.413 --> 00:31:50.584
Good. because I want to present this
proposal to leadership in 30 days.

449
00:31:50.667 --> 00:31:52.628
- Let's make it happen.
- Paul?

450
00:31:57.883 --> 00:32:00.385
- Your services are no longer needed.
- Excuse me?

451
00:32:00.469 --> 00:32:02.679
Let's keep it quiet.
let's keep it cordial.

452
00:32:02.763 --> 00:32:05.390
- Thanks for all your work.
- I'll get my things.

453
00:32:05.474 --> 00:32:07.726
I'll have them sent down
to you in the lobby.

454
00:32:41.510 --> 00:32:42.928
Hello?

455
00:32:44.429 --> 00:32:46.557
Yeah. I'm on my way.

456
00:33:16.253 --> 00:33:18.839
Ah! Oh!

457
00:33:22.175 --> 00:33:24.803
Ah! God!

458
00:33:24.887 --> 00:33:28.390
Ah!

459
00:33:58.462 --> 00:34:00.422
Oh!

460
00:34:03.800 --> 00:34:05.802
Ah!

461
00:34:09.973 --> 00:34:11.224
Ah!

462
00:34:12.392 --> 00:34:13.393
Mm...

463
00:34:18.440 --> 00:34:20.776
Ahh!

464
00:34:20.859 --> 00:34:23.612
God!

465
00:34:30.160 --> 00:34:33.080
It'll be a few minutes.
Please. have a seat.

466
00:34:49.972 --> 00:34:53.016
- How long have you known?
- Two months.

467
00:34:53.100 --> 00:34:55.769
It hasn't impaired my judgment
on the bench.

468
00:34:55.852 --> 00:35:00.357
And it's early on. We don't expect
any real symptoms for quite some time.

469
00:35:00.440 --> 00:35:06.405
I won't be wandering around the Supreme
Court in my boxer shorts anytime soon.

470
00:35:06.488 --> 00:35:11.326
But I'd like to retire now.
long before we get there.

471
00:35:11.410 --> 00:35:14.121
Well. Justice. I want to thank you
for having the courage

472
00:35:14.204 --> 00:35:18.333
to come and share this news with me.
Are you sure the diagnosis is correct?

473
00:35:18.417 --> 00:35:21.628
My doctor's the same
that treated the vice president's wife.

474
00:35:21.712 --> 00:35:24.589
He's the foremost
Alzheimer's specialist in America.

475
00:35:25.590 --> 00:35:27.718
Yes. I made Donald my vice president.

476
00:35:27.801 --> 00:35:30.470
I'd rather him be a pain in my ass here
than over in Congress.

477
00:35:30.554 --> 00:35:33.890
And even the Republicans couldn't
refuse a man who just buried his wife.

478
00:35:33.974 --> 00:35:35.642
Terrible how quickly Marjory went.

479
00:35:35.726 --> 00:35:40.063
I'm telling you this now so you
have time to think about candidates

480
00:35:40.147 --> 00:35:42.733
before I announce my retirement.

481
00:35:42.816 --> 00:35:45.610
- How much time can you give me?
- How much do you need?

482
00:35:45.694 --> 00:35:48.238
I'm about to introduce
America Works to Congress.

483
00:35:48.321 --> 00:35:50.991
It's sure to be an uphill battle.
And I'd prefer not to add

484
00:35:51.074 --> 00:35:53.702
a Supreme Court nomination to the mix.

485
00:35:53.785 --> 00:35:55.871
The Republicans will just
use it as leverage.

486
00:35:55.954 --> 00:35:59.041
I've heard rumblings.
Entitlements on the chopping block?

487
00:35:59.124 --> 00:36:01.251
All the more reason
to keep you on the bench.

488
00:36:01.334 --> 00:36:04.004
It's sure to be challenged
in the Judiciary.

489
00:36:04.087 --> 00:36:08.759
Mr. President.
I want to spend as much time

490
00:36:08.842 --> 00:36:11.344
with my wife as possible

491
00:36:11.428 --> 00:36:15.265
in the good years that I have left.

492
00:36:15.348 --> 00:36:18.393
When Marjory was ill.
she wanted the same thing.

493
00:36:18.477 --> 00:36:21.271
She left the Smithsonian.
and you know what?

494
00:36:21.354 --> 00:36:24.691
She hated every second of being at home.
of not being productive.

495
00:36:24.775 --> 00:36:27.235
of not doing what she loved.

496
00:36:27.319 --> 00:36:30.781
It made her time
with us much harder. and...

497
00:36:31.948 --> 00:36:34.367
it made her deeply unhappy.

498
00:36:34.451 --> 00:36:37.829
Work is the best distraction.
I wish she hadn't retired.

499
00:36:37.913 --> 00:36:41.875
And. uh...
before she lost her lucid thought.

500
00:36:41.958 --> 00:36:43.710
she said she regretted it. too.

501
00:36:43.794 --> 00:36:47.672
Can you give me six months?
A year at the most? That's all.

502
00:36:47.756 --> 00:36:50.175
Just enough time
to get this program up and running

503
00:36:50.258 --> 00:36:52.844
before I have
to face a Supreme Court fight.

504
00:36:55.555 --> 00:36:57.557
- I need to think it over.
- Oh. of course.

505
00:36:57.641 --> 00:37:00.310
- Speak to your wife.
- I'll walk you out.

506
00:37:04.815 --> 00:37:08.151
- I better get that research center.
- Yes. a deal is a deal.

507
00:37:08.235 --> 00:37:10.862
Now. good God. Donald.
let's get something done.

508
00:37:14.616 --> 00:37:16.910
Now you see why Donald said yes.

509
00:37:16.993 --> 00:37:20.664
He may hate my guts. but there's
nothing like a death in the family

510
00:37:20.747 --> 00:37:22.958
to separate the wheat from the bullshit.

511
00:37:23.041 --> 00:37:24.042
Send him in.

512
00:37:24.126 --> 00:37:25.836
Yes. sir.

513
00:37:25.919 --> 00:37:28.171
The president is ready to see you now.

514
00:37:48.525 --> 00:37:50.110
Doug.

515
00:37:51.778 --> 00:37:53.446
Mr. President.

516
00:37:55.615 --> 00:37:58.368
The doctor told me your recovery
is going very well.

517
00:37:58.451 --> 00:38:00.120
Yeah. Well. there's this.

518
00:38:00.203 --> 00:38:02.247
But everything else is as good as new.

519
00:38:02.330 --> 00:38:04.416
It's great to see you.

520
00:38:04.499 --> 00:38:06.376
Claire and I have been
worried sick about you.

521
00:38:06.459 --> 00:38:07.669
Thank you for the gifts.

522
00:38:07.752 --> 00:38:09.296
- Well...
- For looking out for me.

523
00:38:09.379 --> 00:38:12.215
I don't have that many close friends.
I count you among them.

524
00:38:13.216 --> 00:38:17.012
- I appreciate your saying that. sir.
- Oh. drop the "sir." We're old pals.

525
00:38:18.096 --> 00:38:19.556
Well...

526
00:38:20.432 --> 00:38:23.059
I'm the one who should apologize.

527
00:38:23.143 --> 00:38:26.354
You gave me another chance.
You trusted me.

528
00:38:27.564 --> 00:38:29.774
And what happened.
I take responsibility for that.

529
00:38:29.858 --> 00:38:32.652
- No. for putting you in that position.
- Stop. It's not necessary.

530
00:38:32.736 --> 00:38:35.238
- I endangered you just as...
- Yeah. but all I care about

531
00:38:35.322 --> 00:38:38.158
is that you are alive
and getting better.

532
00:38:38.241 --> 00:38:40.285
Let the rest of it go.

533
00:38:41.661 --> 00:38:44.247
- You know how devoted I am.
- You don't have to say it.

534
00:38:44.331 --> 00:38:46.625
You proved it time and time again.

535
00:38:46.708 --> 00:38:48.418
Now. come on. come on. sit down.

536
00:38:50.170 --> 00:38:51.671
Right here.

537
00:39:14.110 --> 00:39:16.821
I should've taken care of her
when I had the chance.

538
00:39:19.824 --> 00:39:21.451
I haven't found her yet.

539
00:39:22.494 --> 00:39:25.872
But when I do. I'll make sure
that no one else does.

540
00:39:25.956 --> 00:39:27.916
You can count on that. sir.

541
00:39:30.043 --> 00:39:31.628
How is it. uh...?

542
00:39:31.711 --> 00:39:33.755
Probably better
if we don't talk about it.

543
00:39:33.838 --> 00:39:35.590
Right. of course.

544
00:39:38.301 --> 00:39:40.887
Well. they told me you needed to see me.

545
00:39:42.973 --> 00:39:46.685
Well. sir. I...
I know that it's a lot to ask.

546
00:39:46.768 --> 00:39:50.188
and that I probably don't deserve it.
considering the mess I put us in.

547
00:39:50.272 --> 00:39:53.108
And I'm sure you have your doubts.

548
00:39:53.191 --> 00:39:55.568
I realize it couldn't
be anything too visible. but...

549
00:39:55.652 --> 00:39:57.529
I've been following everything
with America Works.

550
00:39:57.612 --> 00:40:01.241
- Oh. Well. that's a ways off.
- But I was thinking that I could help.

551
00:40:02.117 --> 00:40:05.203
There should be a targeted plan
for lobbying committee leadership.

552
00:40:05.287 --> 00:40:06.871
And I can work with the political team.

553
00:40:06.955 --> 00:40:09.165
coordinate with House leg directors.
chiefs of staff...

554
00:40:09.249 --> 00:40:12.752
I was in Gaffney yesterday.
visiting my father's grave.

555
00:40:13.628 --> 00:40:15.547
He never took care of himself.

556
00:40:15.630 --> 00:40:20.176
He ignored his heart problems
and... he paid the price.

557
00:40:21.928 --> 00:40:24.931
You have to respect
your own mortality. Doug.

558
00:40:25.015 --> 00:40:27.309
I don't want to be standing
over your grave.

559
00:40:27.392 --> 00:40:29.436
Now. look...

560
00:40:29.519 --> 00:40:33.815
There is a place
for you here. I promise.

561
00:40:33.898 --> 00:40:35.984
But we have to go about this slowly.

562
00:40:36.067 --> 00:40:39.029
I'll work from home.
Only direct contact with you or Remy.

563
00:40:39.112 --> 00:40:40.913
You know the way
that you can help me the best

564
00:40:40.947 --> 00:40:42.824
is to do exactly
what you're doing right now.

565
00:40:42.907 --> 00:40:44.659
focusing on your recovery.

566
00:40:44.743 --> 00:40:49.205
I would never forgive myself if I
put too much on your plate too soon.

567
00:40:52.792 --> 00:40:54.127
You're right.

568
00:40:55.920 --> 00:40:57.589
I'm sorry.

569
00:41:04.888 --> 00:41:05.889
Thank you.

570
00:41:05.972 --> 00:41:07.599
I'm sorry. I have to go.

571
00:41:07.682 --> 00:41:10.435
But look. I meant what I said.

572
00:41:10.518 --> 00:41:13.104
When you are truly ready.

573
00:41:13.188 --> 00:41:14.564
Yes. sir.

574
00:41:15.482 --> 00:41:17.275
Stay as long as you like.

575
00:41:35.960 --> 00:41:40.131
Three hours ago. we pinpointed him here.
in the Shabwa region of Yemen.

576
00:41:40.965 --> 00:41:41.965
Cooperation?

577
00:41:42.008 --> 00:41:44.219
I spoke to the foreign minister
a few minutes ago.

578
00:41:44.302 --> 00:41:46.388
- Civilians?
- Two dozen. non-IDs.

579
00:41:46.471 --> 00:41:48.098
That's too many.

580
00:41:48.181 --> 00:41:51.059
Our concern is that he could
be on the move at any moment.

581
00:41:51.142 --> 00:41:53.103
Sir. with Petrov
coming to Washington...

582
00:41:53.186 --> 00:41:55.522
It's taken us two years
to track Abdullah down.

583
00:41:55.605 --> 00:41:58.191
We can't ignore every opportunity
between now and the summit.

584
00:41:59.859 --> 00:42:01.319
Do you have eyes on the village?

585
00:42:01.403 --> 00:42:04.864
Yes. sir. He's in this building here.

586
00:42:04.948 --> 00:42:07.575
Kill zone is anyone within 50 meters.

587
00:42:09.828 --> 00:42:13.039
If we take him out with no civilian
casualties. I'll authorize the strike.

588
00:42:13.123 --> 00:42:14.791
Sir. if I may. I really think...

589
00:42:14.874 --> 00:42:18.711
President Petrov is coming
to Washington in less than two months.

590
00:42:18.795 --> 00:42:21.798
Our entire Middle East policy
hinges on that meeting.

591
00:42:21.881 --> 00:42:25.218
We don't want to give
the Muslim community any viable reasons

592
00:42:25.301 --> 00:42:27.971
to obstruct things if we can avoid it.

593
00:42:28.054 --> 00:42:30.055
So find a way to do this
without killing civilians.

594
00:42:30.056 --> 00:42:31.099
Thank you all very much.

595
00:42:31.182 --> 00:42:35.103
May I have a moment?
It's about Claire.

596
00:42:35.186 --> 00:42:38.857
If your husband nominates you.
I can't pull any punches.

597
00:42:38.940 --> 00:42:41.401
Lack of experience. Nepotism.

598
00:42:41.484 --> 00:42:43.027
That's right.

599
00:42:43.111 --> 00:42:48.116
- And you think I'm a dilettante.
- No. But plenty of people will.

600
00:42:48.199 --> 00:42:50.326
I've been preparing
since Francis took office.

601
00:42:50.410 --> 00:42:54.164
What I lack in experience
I'll make up for in work ethic.

602
00:42:54.247 --> 00:42:55.915
Why Ambassador to the UN?

603
00:42:55.999 --> 00:42:58.209
You wield far more influence
as the First Lady.

604
00:42:58.293 --> 00:43:01.045
That's not the same
as contributing in a concrete way.

605
00:43:01.129 --> 00:43:03.631
If we vote down your confirmation.

606
00:43:03.715 --> 00:43:08.261
are you comfortable
with that sort of public embarrassment?

607
00:43:08.344 --> 00:43:09.846
I know that's a risk.

608
00:43:12.140 --> 00:43:15.602
- You're running in 2016. right?
- No comment.

609
00:43:15.685 --> 00:43:18.062
Francis and I are impressed

610
00:43:18.146 --> 00:43:20.982
by how the Republicans
are consolidating around you.

611
00:43:21.065 --> 00:43:22.400
You'll make a good candidate.

612
00:43:22.484 --> 00:43:24.986
Not by linking arms
with the president's wife.

613
00:43:25.069 --> 00:43:29.824
If I'm a disaster.
it makes for a good campaign ad.

614
00:43:29.908 --> 00:43:32.368
If I do a good job.
nobody can fault you.

615
00:43:32.452 --> 00:43:35.622
Either way.
it doesn't hurt your chances in 2016.

616
00:43:37.582 --> 00:43:41.336
Well. I appreciate you
coming by before going public.

617
00:43:41.419 --> 00:43:44.631
It is classy. and thoughtful.

618
00:43:45.465 --> 00:43:47.467
I won't actively block you.

619
00:43:47.550 --> 00:43:49.969
The rest is on your shoulders.

620
00:43:50.929 --> 00:43:53.097
Thank you. Senator.

621
00:43:53.598 --> 00:43:56.434
Tell the president I'm doing this
out of respect to you.

622
00:43:57.393 --> 00:43:59.646
Frank's still on my shit list
till I beat him in the general.

623
00:43:59.729 --> 00:44:01.147
I will.

624
00:44:02.232 --> 00:44:04.317
Why didn't you come right away?

625
00:44:04.400 --> 00:44:06.444
I had a meeting I couldn't miss.

626
00:44:06.528 --> 00:44:08.029
Fucking Washington.

627
00:44:08.112 --> 00:44:10.573
- This is gonna hurt.
- I know.

628
00:44:12.367 --> 00:44:14.911
Ah!

629
00:44:15.537 --> 00:44:17.997
Here's some Percocet.
It'll help with the pain.

630
00:44:19.332 --> 00:44:21.125
I'll write you a 30-day prescription.

631
00:44:21.209 --> 00:44:22.585
I can't.

632
00:44:22.669 --> 00:44:25.004
- I'm not supposed to...
- What was that?

633
00:44:27.423 --> 00:44:29.092
Nothing.

634
00:44:37.850 --> 00:44:39.602
All right. You're good to go.

635
00:45:18.683 --> 00:45:20.226
Hey.

636
00:45:20.310 --> 00:45:22.770
- How did it go with Mendoza?
- Well. I think.

637
00:45:22.854 --> 00:45:24.314
He'll support you?

638
00:45:24.397 --> 00:45:26.816
He won't openly fight it.

639
00:45:26.899 --> 00:45:29.068
Well. that is a big step forward.

640
00:45:29.152 --> 00:45:31.863
- How did it go with Doug?
- No real news.

641
00:45:34.615 --> 00:45:36.284
Hey. are you in here again tonight?

642
00:45:36.367 --> 00:45:39.704
I'm still getting over this cold.
I don't want to get you sick.

643
00:45:39.787 --> 00:45:41.581
Well. don't stay up
with all that too late.

644
00:45:41.664 --> 00:45:43.750
Francis?

645
00:45:43.833 --> 00:45:46.085
When do we announce the nomination?

646
00:45:50.798 --> 00:45:53.092
Listen. I wasn't gonna
bring this up tonight.

647
00:45:53.176 --> 00:45:55.762
but you should know
that there are some serious doubts

648
00:45:55.845 --> 00:45:57.764
from people at the State Department.

649
00:45:57.847 --> 00:45:59.515
You mean Cathy.

650
00:45:59.599 --> 00:46:01.392
And some on her staff.

651
00:46:03.936 --> 00:46:05.104
Like what?

652
00:46:05.188 --> 00:46:08.775
Well. in over your head.
wearing two hats. the obvious things.

653
00:46:08.858 --> 00:46:11.986
And are you saying this
because you don't want to move forward?

654
00:46:12.070 --> 00:46:15.156
Not at all. I'm sharing with you
so you fully understand

655
00:46:15.239 --> 00:46:18.534
- what you're getting into.
- And I do.

656
00:46:24.082 --> 00:46:26.167
Maybe we shouldn't rush this.

657
00:46:28.127 --> 00:46:31.255
- You're having doubts now. too.
- I didn't say that.

658
00:46:31.339 --> 00:46:33.100
Only you should put
more thought into whether

659
00:46:33.174 --> 00:46:36.010
this is the right move for you.
That's all.

660
00:46:37.512 --> 00:46:38.805
Good night. Francis.

661
00:46:40.598 --> 00:46:41.808
Feel better.

662
00:47:53.796 --> 00:47:55.465
Francis.

663
00:47:57.008 --> 00:47:59.677
I want you to announce
the nomination this week.

664
00:47:59.760 --> 00:48:02.763
I don't want to wait.
The timing will never be good.

665
00:48:02.847 --> 00:48:04.182
And I don't want to waste time

666
00:48:04.265 --> 00:48:06.305
when I can be getting
real experience under my belt.

667
00:48:06.350 --> 00:48:09.770
So set a date. hold a press conference.
and let's do it.

668
00:48:18.029 --> 00:48:19.280
Claire!

669
00:48:19.363 --> 00:48:23.743
I was not trying to suggest
that you not be the ambassador

670
00:48:23.826 --> 00:48:26.412
- when I brought up Cathy. I was just...
- We made a deal.

671
00:48:26.496 --> 00:48:28.372
and now you're trying
to back away from it.

672
00:48:28.456 --> 00:48:30.541
- That is not true.
- Then you would've told Cathy

673
00:48:30.625 --> 00:48:32.502
it's happening
to make her peace with that.

674
00:48:32.585 --> 00:48:35.463
- It's not that simple.
- Yes. it is.

675
00:48:35.546 --> 00:48:39.342
- You're the president.
- I can't control Congress.

676
00:48:39.425 --> 00:48:42.094
I'm trying to get two
major initiatives off the ground

677
00:48:42.178 --> 00:48:44.305
and every move I make
will have an effect.

678
00:48:44.388 --> 00:48:47.850
We agreed to this before we ever
stepped foot in this house.

679
00:48:47.934 --> 00:48:50.603
- I know what we agreed to.
- How am I supposed to run for office

680
00:48:50.686 --> 00:48:53.481
at some point if I don't have
a legitimate track record?

681
00:48:53.564 --> 00:48:57.026
We have to survive
the next 18 months.

682
00:48:57.109 --> 00:49:00.780
accomplish something.
and then look ahead.

683
00:49:02.657 --> 00:49:04.992
Francis. let's be realistic.

684
00:49:06.118 --> 00:49:08.579
There's no guarantee you'll get elected.

685
00:49:08.663 --> 00:49:10.790
I need to be prepared if you don't.

686
00:49:10.873 --> 00:49:12.833
You have that much faith in me. do you?

687
00:49:12.917 --> 00:49:14.835
More faith than you have in me.
it seems.

688
00:49:14.919 --> 00:49:17.004
I believe in you
more than anyone. Claire.

689
00:49:17.088 --> 00:49:19.799
Then show it. Nominate me.
I shouldn't have to convince you.

690
00:49:19.882 --> 00:49:21.384
It's not about convincing.

691
00:49:21.467 --> 00:49:24.512
It's about being honest
about the political climate

692
00:49:24.595 --> 00:49:27.848
- that we find ourselves...
- I'm almost 50 years old.

693
00:49:27.932 --> 00:49:30.309
I've been in the passenger seat
for decades.

694
00:49:30.393 --> 00:49:32.103
It's time for me
to get behind the wheel.

695
00:49:32.186 --> 00:49:35.982
That needs to start now.
Before the election.

696
00:49:36.065 --> 00:49:38.818
Because who knows what will happen?
What if you lose?

697
00:49:41.988 --> 00:49:45.783
I will not be
a placeholder president. Claire.

698
00:49:47.618 --> 00:49:52.290
I will win.
And I will leave a legacy.

699
00:49:52.373 --> 00:49:54.125
You mean we will.

700
00:49:54.208 --> 00:49:55.501
Excuse me. sir.

701
00:49:55.585 --> 00:49:58.421
The Secretary of Defense is on the line.
He says it's urgent.

702
00:50:02.216 --> 00:50:03.217
Yes?

703
00:50:05.469 --> 00:50:07.096
Okay.

704
00:50:07.179 --> 00:50:08.639
I'm coming.

705
00:50:08.723 --> 00:50:10.266
Not until I get there.

706
00:50:10.349 --> 00:50:12.351
- I'll be right down.
- Yes. sir.

707
00:50:18.274 --> 00:50:20.359
Get dressed.
I want you to see something.

708
00:51:17.667 --> 00:51:19.126
Come in.

709
00:51:32.181 --> 00:51:34.016
- Here.
- Thank you.

710
00:51:36.686 --> 00:51:38.062
Okay. great.

711
00:51:39.355 --> 00:51:40.523
Get undressed.

712
00:52:38.789 --> 00:52:40.708
How did this happen?

713
00:52:40.791 --> 00:52:42.460
Doesn't matter.

714
00:52:53.763 --> 00:52:55.347
Let me help you.

715
00:53:05.608 --> 00:53:07.568
Sh... I'll... I'll do it.

716
00:53:22.082 --> 00:53:23.501
I'll be gentle.

717
00:53:29.298 --> 00:53:31.300
Don't be gentle.

718
00:53:32.092 --> 00:53:33.594
Like that?

719
00:53:34.595 --> 00:53:36.096
Yeah.

720
00:53:46.106 --> 00:53:49.026
- Oh. whoa! What the fuck?
- It's bourbon.

721
00:53:49.109 --> 00:53:52.112
- I...
- That's all. It's just bourbon.

722
00:53:52.196 --> 00:53:54.448
- Take it.
- I really don't want to.

723
00:53:54.532 --> 00:53:57.117
Nothing's going through the skin.

724
00:53:57.201 --> 00:53:59.620
I just want you to squirt it...

725
00:53:59.703 --> 00:54:01.330
into my mouth.

726
00:54:02.540 --> 00:54:05.084
Okay? Please.

727
00:54:16.345 --> 00:54:18.305
- Is that our target?
- Yes. sir.

728
00:54:18.389 --> 00:54:21.350
Mr. President.
this is a highly classified operation...

729
00:54:21.433 --> 00:54:24.019
I'm clearing the First Lady
for this operation.

730
00:54:24.103 --> 00:54:25.729
Yes. sir. Forgive me. sir.

731
00:54:25.813 --> 00:54:27.690
We are armed and ready. sir.

732
00:54:27.773 --> 00:54:31.193
Abdullah is in one of those
vehicles. We can't tell which one.

733
00:54:31.277 --> 00:54:32.945
If they go in
three different directions.

734
00:54:33.028 --> 00:54:36.282
we wouldn't know where to strike. and
if he makes it back to the mountains.

735
00:54:36.365 --> 00:54:38.075
we'll lose our satellite track on him.

736
00:54:39.451 --> 00:54:41.078
Are those children?

737
00:54:41.161 --> 00:54:43.497
I can't say definitely. sir.
but they could be.

738
00:54:45.833 --> 00:54:47.376
Do we have authorization. sir?

739
00:54:50.045 --> 00:54:53.090
- Proceed.
- Proceed with the launch.

740
00:54:55.467 --> 00:54:57.261
And ten seconds.

741
00:54:59.013 --> 00:55:04.018
And five. four. three...

742
00:55:14.028 --> 00:55:16.280
